# Hub expand motion — do not regress

## Top circular rings (Calories / Steps / Sleep)

- Live in `HubRingBay` (`src/components/hub/HubRingBay.tsx`). Prefer editing that file for ring layout/motion.
- On expand of any ring: **siblings fade/scale away** (`opacity-0`, `scale-90`); the **active ring slides to horizontal center** via absolute `left` + transform (not `justify-content`, which cannot animate).
- On collapse: reverse the same transition (~760ms).
- Do **not** replace this with `flex justify-around` + opacity dimming only.
- Do **not** remount a second ProgressRing as the “centered” copy for steps/sleep; one instance per ring must morph in place.
- Calories expand chrome (`CaloriesExpandShell`) must **not** nest a duplicate dial that replaces this bay behavior.

## Protocol / Training rail

- Collapsed: classic **2-column** rail with vial + **Protocol text** on the left and workout ring + **Training text** on the right. Text must remain visible when collapsed.
- Expanded: the **compact rail collapses away** (HubCollapse); the expand panel appears at its **previous destination** with its own vial/ring hero (do **not** `hideHero`, do **not** slide rail glyphs to center).
- Animate with HubCollapse / HubPresence — do not invent a center-morph for protocol/training.

## Shared-element morph (steps bars, etc.)

- Steps chart / readiness: keep mounted and use `HubCollapse` — do not `return null` to hide siblings (that remounts and respawns animations).
